work.work-title: As with gladness men of old

credit.credit-words: As with joyful steps they sped To that lowly manger bed There to bend the knee before Him whom Heaven and earth adore; So may we with willing feet Ever seek Thy mercy seat.
As they offered gifts most rare At that manger rude and bare; So may we with holy joy, Pure and free from sin's alloy, All our costliest treasures bring, Christ, to Thee, our heavenly king.
As with gladness men of old
